1 diabetes are enrolled and that charter schools otherwise comply with
2 G.S. 115C-375.3.
3 (6) The Department of Public Instruction shall ensure that charter schools comply
4 with G.S. 115C-375.2A. The board of directors of a charter school shall
5 provide the school with a supply of emergency epinephrine auto-injectors
6 delivery systems necessary to meet the requirements of G.S. 115C-375.2A."
7 SECTION 2.(b) G.S. 115C-238.66(7) reads as rewritten:
8 "(7) Health and safety. – The board of directors shall require that the regional
9 school meet the same health and safety standards required of a local school
10 administrative unit.
11 The Department of Public Instruction shall ensure that regional schools
12 comply with G.S. 115C-375.2A. The board of directors of a regional school
13 shall provide the school with a supply of emergency epinephrine
14 auto-injectors delivery systems necessary to carry out the provisions of
15 G.S. 115C-375.2A."
16 SECTION 3. This act is effective when it becomes law and applies beginning with
17 the 2025-2026 school year.
